0.title: Rules
0.body:
Welcome to Wheel of Fortune! Mod by TrashCat.

[b]How to Play[/b]
* One player will be the word master either by choice or everyone can take turns going around the table and being the word master. 

* Once that player is chosen, all others must put on a blindfold (Press B). The word master will pull the cards out of the infinity bags to spell out his puzzle and flip them upside down on the game board.

* Once the word master is finished, he will give the queue to take your blindfolds off. Everyone then takes turns starting clockwise from the word master's seat. (Put Turn Mode on)

[b]Turns[/b]
* At the start of your turn, you may either Spin the Wheel or Guess the Puzzle. Spin the Wheel by using the Flick tool. As long as you don't land on Lose A Turn or Bankrupt, you can guess any consonant in the alphabet. 

* You will get the dollar amount shown multiplied by how many correct letters there are on the board (A $300 space will give you $900 if you guess a T and three T are on the board). 

* Once this is completed, you can then Spin the Wheel again, Buy a Vowel, or Guess the Puzzle. Buying a Vowel will cost you $250 from your current round total regardless of how many vowels are shown. 

* If at any time you fail to guess a consonant, vowel, or the puzzle, then your turn ends and it will be the next player's turn. 

[b]Winning[/b]
* A player will win once he or she correctly guesses the puzzle. Only the winner of the round will keep their money total that was earned during the round and all other players will not gain anything for that round. 

* Use the money scorecards in front of every player by clicking "Set State" and putting in the correct amount. Zero is in state 10. This should show your grand total saved between rounds and bankruptcy does not affect this total. 

* For keeping track of scores during the round, simply use the text tool and update as necessary in front of your player. Add the round total to your money scorecard if you win the round.
